<p>Super rich and silky, this savory avocado sauce is a dream to add to any variety of pasta for an easy meal. Also delicious on salads or veggies!</p>

<p>Makes 4 servings</p>

<p>Total 20 minutes</p>

<h3 id="ingredients">Ingredients</h3>

<ul>
  <li>1 large avocado</li>
  <li>1-4 cloves garlic (raw or roasted)</li>
  <li>3/4 cup warm pasta water (from cooking the pasta)</li>
  <li>2 Tbsp white miso paste</li>
  <li>1/2 cup raw walnuts</li>
  <li>2 lemons, juiced pinch of zest</li>
  <li>big handful of greens (basil or other leafy greens like kale, arugula, spinach, parsley)</li>
  <li>nutritional yeast to taste â€“ fold into pasta directly (I like to add a lot!)</li>
  <li>optional: for a hint of sweet, add 2-3 tsp maple syrup to the sauce</li>
  <li>salt and pepper to taste (optional - I usually add 1/2 tsp salt and pepper each)</li>
  <li>topping: nutritional yeast, red pepper flakes, greens garnish</li>
